    {
      "id": "field-node-class-smoke-overview",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Node Class Smoke",
      "position": {
        "x": -480,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "# Field-Driven Node Class Smoke\n\nThis graph is itself a candidate node-class artifact under the new regime.\n\nWhat it should prove:\n- graph identity and doctrine live on the declaration\n- machine-readable contract data lives in field nodes\n- human explanation lives in markdown\n- inline `view` nodes can still describe node/editor payloads without becoming semantic authority"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "field-node-class-smoke-spec",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Expected Readout",
      "position": {
        "x": 1120,
        "y": -260
      },
      "width": 560,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Expected Readout\n\nReader expectations:\n- `nodeType` => `smoke.card`\n- defaults.label => `Smoke Card`\n- defaults.size.width => `360`\n- defaults.size.height => `220`\n- overrides.allowPorts => `true`\n- node view => inline `node.web.detail` view node\n- editor view => inline `editor.web` view node\n\nNo manifest or dictionary node is required to make sense of this artifact."
      }
    },
